task.summary: Added initial grammar derived and simplified somewhat from the existing cocu grammar.
Created first somewhat working version of an implementation of an open message protocol.

Created first, more than, somewhat working version of an implementation of an open message protocol.
Here, an message processing behavior for a single message is examplified and working.
var myObject = #{ var envelope = receive reply: envelope, "A reply" } myObject.msg

Created message processing example of two subsequent message receivals
var myObject = #{ var envelope = receive reply: envelope, "A reply" envelope = receive reply: envelope, "Another reply" } var firstReply = myObject.msg var secondReply = myObject.msg

Added naive support for simple match expressions. - Only key-based like switch statements in Java, except as expressions.
E.g.
match "Hello" Case: "Hello" Then' 1 Case: "Bye" Then' 2
Yields
1

Generalized match expressions to include support for integer keys. - which can be mixed with string keys.
match: 100 Case: 2 Then' 1 Case: "aMsg2" Then' 2 Case: 100 Then' 200

Finished first revision of signaling.
E.g.
try' signal: "stuff" Catch' |aCtx aSignal| (resume: aCtx With: "Resumed with some value")
yields
"Resumed with some value"
since tryCatch is an expression
The use og signal: "stuff" forwards control to the handler in catch, with then resumes (sends back the control) with a supplied value to the try body, which then in return yields the supplied value ("Resumed with some value").
